<subSubSection pageId="649" pageNumber="650" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="649.[136,778,785,1526]" pageId="649" pageNumber="650">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1228,1254]" pageId="649" pageNumber="650">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name is derived from the Greek 
<emphasis box="[136,192,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="649" pageNumber="650">scari</emphasis>
(=a little worm) and - 
<emphasis box="[437,523,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="649" pageNumber="650">delphys</emphasis>
, alluding to the wormlike body form of the new genus. Gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="649" pageNumber="650" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="649.[136,778,785,1526]" pageId="649" pageNumber="650">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,298,1330,1356]" pageId="649" pageNumber="650">Remarks</emphasis>
. Within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" box="[439,621,1329,1355]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="649" pageNumber="650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodelphyidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[633,778,1329,1355]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scaridelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="649" pageNumber="650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[633,778,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="649" pageNumber="650">Scaridelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[136,245,1364,1390]" pageId="649" pageNumber="650" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,239,1364,1390]" pageId="649" pageNumber="650">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the most simplified body. The new genus may be compared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[442,577,1397,1423]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="649" pageNumber="650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,577,1397,1423]" italics="true" pageId="649" pageNumber="650">Haplostatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the extreme reduction of the mouthparts but further reductions occur in the new genus, i.e., it lacks the rostrum and antenna and has a small, unsegmented urosome.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
